watch that, but once we have

00:01:19.650 --> 00:01:22.180
our correct exposure, now we

00:01:22.270 --> 00:01:23.650
are going to simply to take a

00:01:23.760 --> 00:01:25.120
shot, and the thing

00:01:25.530 --> 00:01:26.810
to remember when you take a shot is

00:01:26.940 --> 00:01:28.610
unless you're using

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:30.400
back-button focus with camera,

00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:31.610
you're going to try and take a

00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:32.780
shot with ExpoDisc over the

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:33.800
lens and it's going to

00:01:33.880 --> 00:01:35.060
be like &amp;lt;whirring noise&amp;gt; it's going

00:01:35.210 --> 00:01:36.120
to be making some really hard noises

00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:37.860
because it's not going to be able to focus.

00:01:38.260 --> 00:01:39.330
So what you simply do

00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:40.840
is you can switch your camera's focus

00:01:41.260 --> 00:01:43.570
to manual focus take a

00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:44.900
shot and then simply

00:01:45.450 --> 00:01:47.220
just make sure you put it back to autofocus.

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:48.550
The next step is you want

00:01:48.770 --> 00:01:49.850
to double check and make sure

00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:52.250
that that exposure that you just took is correct.

00:01:52.650 --> 00:01:53.650
So, you're going to look

00:01:53.860 --> 00:01:55.320
at the back of your camera and

00:01:55.470 --> 00:01:56.670
look at your histogram, if you

00:01:56.870 --> 00:01:57.830
see the spike down the middle

00:01:58.360 --> 00:01:59.560
or close to the middle you

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:01.620
know that you're in that sweet spot that you want to be.

00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:03.180
The next thing of what you're

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:04.160
going to do is you're actually

00:02:04.490 --> 00:02:05.810
going to apply that color

00:02:06.130 --> 00:02:07.590
in your camera, from Canon

00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:09.320
to Nikon users the process

00:02:10.050 --> 00:02:11.260
varies, so make sure that

00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:12.620
you check your manual on how

00:02:12.930 --> 00:02:14.630
to apply that custom color right in your camera.

00:02:15.690 --> 00:02:16.610
So go ahead and check that out,

00:02:17.060 --> 00:02:18.420
and then now you're ready to

00:02:18.580 --> 00:02:19.770
shoot your subject and you'll get

00:02:20.130 --> 00:02:21.600
great color right inside your camera.

